alternatives.transcript: this is palmer who is a sixty two year old female with a history of pulmonary sarcoid and hypertension she comes to the ed today with episodes of shortness of breath near syncope as well as fatigue and palpitations and orthopnea she says that this has been going on for about two months and worsening since onset she saw her primary care physician for her symptoms about three days ago and had had some tests done she's unsure of what tests were done and she hasn't gotten those results back yet she called them today due to exacerbation of her symptoms and was referred to the er she says that her her symptoms are exacerbated with most of her activity she notes that she was previously very active walking about five times a week but now is unable to do that due to her symptoms she also notes orthopnea noting that she is now sleeping in the recliner due to shortness of breath when lying flat she denies any loss of consciousness she denies chest pain she does endorse an eight pound weight gain in the past two weeks as well as some lower extremity swelling she also endorses some subjective wheezing her history as i said she has a pulmonary sarcoidosis which she is on chronic prednisone ten milligrams she also has hypertension for which she's on lisinopril ten milligrams a day she had a clean cardiac cath about a year ago after an abnormal ekg or pcp she denies tobacco use alcohol illicit drug use she lives at home with her husband who she says is supportive she does have insurance for her job as a fourth grade teacher vitals were significant for slight tachycardia at a hundred and ten with slight hypertension at one thirty six over ninety nine her sp o two was slightly hypoxic at ninety one percent she was eight fibro physical exam was significant for a systolic murmur with an s four gallop she did have positive jvd but no carotid bruise she had bibasilar rales and wheeze in her lungs in both lungs she did have one plus pedal edema with no cap tenderness and negative hohman's sign labs were remarkable for an elevated troponin of four thousand or or elevated bmp of four thousand i'm sorry and a negative troponin chest x-ray showed mediasinal fullness consistent with pulmonary sarcoid she had no cardiomegaly and no pulmonary edema ekg did show a sinus tachycardia at a rate of about a hundred she had a normal axis she did have a run of non sustained b tach on the ekg but her rhythm in the room was a normal sinus echo did show restrictive cardiomyopathy with increased wall thickness ef was normal at fifty five percent i believe that her symptoms are due to sarcoidosis restrictive cardiomyopathy with an nyha scale of three for her i would like to admit her to telemetry and give her endoderm for the non sustained v tach keep her on her bisinopril and increase her prednisone dose to sixty milligrams a day po i also would like to give forty milligrams of furosemide iv for fluid overload as far as labs i would like to order a cmp to keep an eye on her potassium because we're giving that furosemide i don't believe she needs any diagnostic imaging orders at this time but i do want to consult radiology for a possible fdg pet scan to look at the infiltrates in her heart i would also like to consult interventional cardiology for an a for a possible aicd placement given the nsvt
